io.pivotal.rti.protocols

Annotation Type ProtocolDetail


  • @Documented
@Inherited
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface ProtocolDetail
    Annotation to let RTI discover new fields contributed through ProtocolAdapter implementations. This is used in conjunction with ProtocolDetails.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      java.lang.String name
      Name of the field contributed to RTI Data Dictionary.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      java.lang.String description
      Description of the new field contributed.
      java.lang.Class<?> type
      Type class of the new field contributed.

    • Element Detail

      • name

        public abstract java.lang.String name
        Name of the field contributed to RTI Data Dictionary. This is a mandatory field.
        Returns:
        name of the field

      • description

        public abstract java.lang.String description
        Description of the new field contributed. A standard descritption text is provided by default.
        Returns:
        description of the field
        Default:
        "Not provided yet"

      • type

        public abstract java.lang.Class<?> type
        Type class of the new field contributed. By default it returns Object.
        Returns:
        type class of the field
        Default:
        java.lang.Object.class
